tion of new cultural ideas possible, while rising incomes and liberal attitudes created a generation of men behaving badly.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 7aART / European.2bisacsh  aLow Countries, Golden Age, youth culture, genderstudies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060672040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048532995zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048532995423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048532995.jpg  a978-3-11-060672-0  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK